Subject: [PATCH 0/4] arm64: dts: allwinner: add A733/Cubie A7S DTS support

Maintainer-shape review export. Do not mail this directory without a final
human review, regeneration from the exact kernel branch, and current
maintainer recipient checks.

This series adds initial DTS support for the Allwinner A733 SoC and the Radxa
Cubie A7S board:

- A733 MMC compatible binding coverage
- Radxa Cubie A7S board compatible
- initial A733 SoC DTSI with CPUs, timer, GICv3, RTC oscillator provider,
  CCU/R-CCU, pinctrl, UART0, and SDMMC0
- Cubie A7S board DTS enabling UART0 console and SD card boot storage

This export intentionally does not carry local CCU/PRCM or pinctrl driver
patches. Those areas overlap active A733 RFC work and should be coordinated as
external prerequisites unless maintainers ask for a different plan. The A733
CCU RFC also depends on the A733 RTC series.

Depends-on: 20260121-a733-rtc-v1-0-d359437f23a7@pigmoral.tech
Depends-on: 20260310-a733-clk-v1-0-36b4e9b24457@pigmoral.tech
Depends-on: 20250821004232.8134-1-andre.przywara@arm.com

Ethernet, VPU/Cedrus, display, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, USB-C, PCIe, and other board
peripherals are intentionally out of scope. Vendor U-Boot workarounds used for
private lab proof collection are not encoded in these device trees.

The corrected-root Cubie A7S runtime proof has been captured in the private
homelab workflow and passes its strict proof gate. The proof shows the exact v4
Image and DTB loading, Linux 7.1.0-rc6-gabc8d07b0a63, Radxa Cubie A7S machine
model, 8 CPUs, GICv3 redistributors, A733 pinctrl/UART0, SDMMC0 enumeration,
mmcblk0 partition discovery, and a read-only mmcblk0p3 root mount via the
corrected PARTUUID path.

The regenerated review branch is stacked on the current local prerequisite
stack that applies the A733 RTC, CCU/PRCM, and pinctrl RFCs. It also aligns the
DTSI with the RTC-derived A733 CCU input API and Andre Przywara RFC 10-bank
A733 pinctrl binding shape.

Open work before mailing:

- re-check the A733 RTC, CCU/PRCM, and pinctrl RFC status before sending
- rerun maintainer-recipient and bisectability checks against the final branch
- perform final human review of trailers, recipients, and cover-letter claims

